contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:09.289 --> 02:11.290
(CHACROW SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

02:13.410 --> 02:16.170
(BOTH SPEAKING ALGONQUIAN)

02:16.250 --> 02:18.530
Did you disturb my wife, Chacrow?

02:18.610 --> 02:20.570
Speak.

02:21.690 --> 02:24.970
When will I be done
with your calling on my family?

02:25.050 --> 02:28.570
Winganuske must visit our village.

02:28.650 --> 02:31.410
You will cease deciding what must be.
Do you understand?

02:31.490 --> 02:34.330
Henry, I have a child.

02:34.410 --> 02:36.730
I carry a baby for you.

02:42.650 --> 02:45.850
Then I will take you
to your Pamunkey kin. No.

02:49.770 --> 02:51.770
Chacrow.

02:51.850 --> 02:54.170
You do not appear a man
who loves such good news.

02:55.170 --> 02:58.370
Why is that? Speak.

03:00.650 --> 03:02.850
Speak.

03:02.930 --> 03:05.890
I will have you tell me
the darkness I see in your eyes.

03:14.130 --> 03:16.130
(SPEAKING ALGONQUIAN)

03:27.410 --> 03:30.810
(ALL CHEERING AND CLAPPING)

03:44.890 --> 03:46.890
Oh!

04:03.610 --> 04:05.530
(APPLAUSE)

04:05.610 --> 04:07.570
(HUMMING)

04:14.210 --> 04:17.810
If only we could all reap
such pleasure in our penance

04:17.890 --> 04:19.850
as Mercy does.
Huh.

04:19.930 --> 04:22.250
It's not the repentance
that fills her heart,

04:22.330 --> 04:24.810
but the sin of getting
herself with child.

04:24.890 --> 04:30.650
Well, the prospect of losing such a
faithful maid must pain you, Jocelyn.

04:30.730 --> 04:33.530
I'll find another girl,
once Mercy is married.

04:33.610 --> 04:35.570
(CONTINUES HUMMING)

04:41.570 --> 04:43.650
Have you summoned
me here, sir, to gloat

04:43.730 --> 04:46.290
that I returned from upriver
empty-handed?

04:46.370 --> 04:48.730
Widow, you were a valiant foe.

04:49.610 --> 04:51.770
For a woman.

04:53.850 --> 04:55.850
Is there still no word, Governor...

04:56.850 --> 04:58.850
..of where Master Crabtree
vanished to?

05:00.490 --> 05:03.970
Defiance might bring
a thrill to your cheek, widow,

05:04.050 --> 05:06.730
but wars are won with might.

05:06.810 --> 05:09.930
I employed scouts and assassins
to follow after him.

05:10.010 --> 05:11.970
The factor is dead.

05:13.770 --> 05:16.170
His body is, this moment,
travelling to us.

05:17.250 --> 05:19.610
Now, I know that
you are defeated, widow,

05:19.690 --> 05:21.650
and you know that you are humbled.

05:22.890 --> 05:25.370
But the world must see it.

05:25.450 --> 05:30.050
From this day hence, you will
curtsey when you approach me.

05:31.970 --> 05:35.370
Now, let's see how you look
when you bend the knee.

05:42.010 --> 05:44.450
(GRUNTS) I think
you can do better than that.

05:46.330 --> 05:48.930
Lower, hm?

05:54.970 --> 05:56.970
Lower.

06:15.250 --> 06:17.250
(SPEAKING ALGONQUIAN)

06:55.330 --> 06:57.330
(ALL WHOOPING)

07:27.970 --> 07:29.970
(HUMMING)

07:32.050 --> 07:36.970
Ma'am, will you be the one who breaks
the cake over my head at my wedding?

07:37.050 --> 07:39.010
(CHUCKLES) Yes.

07:40.290 --> 07:43.210
(SIGHS, CHUCKLES)

07:43.290 --> 07:45.250
I witnessed Master Read

07:45.330 --> 07:48.090
showing his forge to a man
who appeared to be a blacksmith.

07:48.170 --> 07:52.130
Oh, yes, that's the new smithy.
(CONTINUES HUMMING)

07:52.210 --> 07:54.170
Is James Read to take on
an apprentice?

07:54.250 --> 07:56.290
Oh, no, ma'am.
He's selling his forge.

07:56.370 --> 07:59.810
I will make the cake
so that it crumbles up beautiful.

08:00.850 --> 08:04.370
Then James Read intends to take on
another position in Jamestown?

08:05.530 --> 08:11.130
Master Read is leaving, ma'am,
going upriver to another settlement.

08:11.210 --> 08:13.170
(HUMMING)

08:25.090 --> 08:28.250
Have you come to pray to a boulder,
Mistress Rutter?

08:28.330 --> 08:32.010
I saw their king here,
sir. Opechancanough.

08:32.090 --> 08:34.130
He was laying tobacco and the like.

08:34.210 --> 08:37.530
They believe there's a footprint
of one of their gods in the rock.

08:37.610 --> 08:39.610
They say he walked this earth once.

08:39.690 --> 08:42.210
Did they throw
deer hairs into the air?

08:42.289 --> 08:46.330
They tell their children
this will bring new creatures
into the world for them to hunt.

08:46.410 --> 08:49.010
(ALL LAUGHING) YEARDLEY:
The Naturals must be taught

08:49.090 --> 08:51.930
that what they venerate
is untrue and worthless.

08:53.010 --> 08:55.970
When their blasphemous totems
are gone, they will forget them.

08:58.210 --> 09:01.290
What? Are we weak?

09:01.370 --> 09:03.930
Are we to be mocked by their vulgary?

09:05.890 --> 09:09.970
Destroy it. No, sir.
Sir, they were worshipping.

09:18.930 --> 09:20.930
(RUSTLING)

09:25.410 --> 09:27.410
(GASPS)

09:27.490 --> 09:29.450
Tamlin.

09:31.210 --> 09:33.210
Why am I glad to see you?

09:35.370 --> 09:37.370
Tam...

09:39.130 --> 09:42.690
..I will look after you this time.
I promise.

09:44.170 --> 09:46.650
Tamlin...

09:48.050 --> 09:50.690
..won't you come home with me?

09:54.130 --> 09:56.130
Please.

09:59.250 --> 10:01.250
(FLOOR CREAKING)

10:05.570 --> 10:07.570
(DOOR OPENS)

10:30.010 --> 10:32.010
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

10:34.890 --> 10:39.810
Governor, Opechancanough has
changed his name to Mangopeesomon.

10:41.130 --> 10:43.130
That could be a war name.

10:43.210 --> 10:45.730
You should go and enquire,
see what mood they live in.

10:45.810 --> 10:47.770
Do you tell me
how to govern now, Sharrow?

10:49.050 --> 10:51.050
The Naturals are already defeated.

10:51.130 --> 10:53.090
Trade is a weapon
that has tamed them.

10:53.170 --> 10:56.450
God, food and friendship
will bring them to heel.

10:56.530 --> 10:59.490
They kneel in our churches,
they wear our clothes,

10:59.570 --> 11:03.490
they crave our food and fineries.
That is a people crushed.

11:03.570 --> 11:07.690
Governor, the Pamunkey
are a brave, proud nation.

11:07.770 --> 11:10.050
If you believe
them trampled under foot,

11:10.130 --> 11:12.810
then your mind
is diseased with arrogancy.

11:23.730 --> 11:25.730
(CHUCKLES)

11:25.810 --> 11:30.490
Widow, I told you
to curtsey when we met.

11:30.570 --> 11:33.970
Is there reason such rosy conceit
is restored to your cheeks?

11:34.050 --> 11:35.810
Dear Governor,

11:35.890 --> 11:39.010
I am merely taking such pleasure
in the taste of barley sugars.

11:39.090 --> 11:41.730
They appeared in my house after dark.

11:41.810 --> 11:45.610
Oh, but how they fill my mouth
with such a sweet taste of England.

11:46.610 --> 11:51.330
I wonder how they arrived here.
(CHUCKLES)

12:01.610 --> 12:03.610
There he is.

12:04.930 --> 12:09.730
There's the lad.
Didn't I know he would come back?

12:10.730 --> 12:12.730
(SIGHS)

12:15.690 --> 12:18.690
Oh... (STAMMERING)
You're looking fine.

12:40.530 --> 12:43.770
I hear you are to leave us,
Master Read.

12:43.850 --> 12:46.290
When we return from upriver.

12:47.610 --> 12:50.850
I sent word to England

12:50.930 --> 12:53.290
that I was willing to pass on
my forge to...

12:53.370 --> 12:55.330
the man who paid me
the best price for it.

12:57.570 --> 13:00.530
Jamestown is to enjoy
such prosperity.

13:00.610 --> 13:03.970
Our fortunes will grow
as the town and its farms
expand beyond imagining.

13:04.050 --> 13:06.210
I have no argument
with other people's plans,

13:06.290 --> 13:08.250
but they're not mine.

13:08.330 --> 13:11.010
I see a golden sorrow on every face.

13:15.610 --> 13:18.090
When will you leave?

13:18.170 --> 13:21.450
There's no reason to delay,
now that my new smithy's here.

13:22.810 --> 13:24.810
I'll go tomorrow.

13:26.490 --> 13:28.490
James...

13:33.650 --> 13:36.210
Might I give you a memento?
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

13:37.690 --> 13:40.210
You saved my life.

13:40.290 --> 13:42.250
I hope you never forget that.

13:59.010 --> 14:01.210
(BELL TOLLING)

14:05.010 --> 14:07.010
We have received reports

14:07.090 --> 14:09.890
of the unfortunate death
of Master Crabtree.

14:10.890 --> 14:12.890
I bid his body be returned to us,

14:12.970 --> 14:15.330
so that we might offer him
a dignified burial.

14:20.330 --> 14:22.330
(ALL GASPING)

14:26.130 --> 14:28.130
(INDISTINCT MURMURING)

14:30.210 --> 14:32.690
Why is it filled
with pigs' tongues?

14:33.690 --> 14:36.050
They are the mark of a liar.

14:36.130 --> 14:38.090
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

14:39.770 --> 14:44.490
Governor.
Governor, you must witness this.

14:48.930 --> 14:50.930
What kind of jest is this?

14:51.010 --> 14:55.090
Oh, but, sir, you were the one
that had me arrested,

14:55.170 --> 14:58.010
locked up.

14:58.090 --> 15:02.730
Here I am. Governor,
attend what he has upon his finger.

15:02.810 --> 15:05.010
The King's signet.

15:06.970 --> 15:12.570
Kill me if you wish, Governor.
It will not alter your plight.

15:12.650 --> 15:16.130
I have sent news to His Majesty
of what I discovered here.

15:17.170 --> 15:21.050
A new Governor is on the ocean now.

15:22.370 --> 15:26.330
(JOCELYN LAUGHING)

15:30.010 --> 15:33.490
(CONTINUES LAUGHING)
Release him.

16:02.050 --> 16:04.530
Now...

16:04.610 --> 16:09.410
Let me wash your face for you,
so you can see how handsome you are.

16:09.490 --> 16:12.250
(CHUCKLES)

16:12.330 --> 16:14.650
No!

16:14.730 --> 16:16.690
Leave me be.

16:17.850 --> 16:19.850
(CRYING)

16:25.250 --> 16:27.490
What happened to you
out there, child?

16:39.330 --> 16:41.330
(DOOR CLOSING)

16:52.730 --> 16:55.210
REDWICK: James Read!

16:55.290 --> 16:57.450
You are arrested
for the sake of a crime.

16:57.530 --> 17:00.810
What we hear is that
you're leaving the town suddenly,

17:00.890 --> 17:03.570
and the widow's valuable brooch
has been stolen.

17:18.849 --> 17:21.450
PEPPER: Why would the Pamunkey
want war now, Henry?

17:21.530 --> 17:25.050
I hope they don't,
but we will be ready.

17:25.130 --> 17:28.450
We must place barrels such as these
all about the place, Pepper.

17:28.530 --> 17:31.250
Winganuske would say
if there were to be trouble.

17:33.090 --> 17:36.850
Well, people live by deep loyalties.

17:36.930 --> 17:41.370
It may be that her bond is not to me,
but to her own kind.

17:42.770 --> 17:45.690
If the Naturals do come...

17:46.730 --> 17:50.410
..we will show them
we hold a fearsome might.

17:56.410 --> 17:59.610
(MEN SHOUTING)

18:04.450 --> 18:06.650
(SPEAKING ALGONQUIAN)

18:22.570 --> 18:25.570
(MEN SHOUTING)
(WHIMPERING)

18:40.450 --> 18:43.330
(INDISTINCT CALLING AND WHOOPING)

18:46.090 --> 18:48.490
(HEART THUMPING)

18:51.250 --> 18:53.530
(MUFFLED SCREAMING)

19:02.490 --> 19:04.490
Maria.

19:04.570 --> 19:07.450
What is it?

19:07.530 --> 19:09.490
I do not know.

19:11.370 --> 19:14.290
Something is wrong.

19:14.370 --> 19:18.730
But...Pedro, I do not know.

19:20.450 --> 19:22.450
(SHOUTING)

19:35.970 --> 19:37.970
YEARDLEY: My people...

19:39.890 --> 19:43.130
..we are here in Virginia
on the most wondrous mission.

19:43.210 --> 19:46.250
Farms.

19:46.330 --> 19:48.290
Families.

19:48.370 --> 19:50.330
Fortune.

19:52.010 --> 19:56.330
We are the conquerors
and the conjurors of a new world.

19:58.210 --> 20:01.650
And I know what we create here

20:01.730 --> 20:05.410
will be founded on our love
of the old country.

20:08.890 --> 20:13.330
We will fill our fields
with many, many great men,

20:13.410 --> 20:15.370
like Pedro.

20:17.090 --> 20:19.850
We have set in motion
what is to be.

20:21.130 --> 20:24.130
And so my calling here...

20:25.490 --> 20:28.090
..my service to you is done.

20:31.410 --> 20:33.810
I am standing down as your Governor.

20:35.290 --> 20:39.170
A new Head of Virginia
is aboard a ship,

20:39.250 --> 20:43.170
crossing the ocean,
to take up this proud office.

20:43.250 --> 20:45.410
What is certain...

20:46.610 --> 20:48.730
..what is beyond doubting...

20:49.930 --> 20:52.730
..is that our noble cause here
is riding to triumph.

20:54.410 --> 20:57.970
So go to your farms,
to your businesses...

20:58.970 --> 21:02.570
..and thank the heavens
that we are English.

21:04.290 --> 21:06.290
(CROWD MUTTERING)

21:10.050 --> 21:13.890
Your appearance suggests that you
are the one being deposed, Marshall.

21:13.970 --> 21:16.890
I have just heard
who is to be our new Governor.

21:16.970 --> 21:20.450
Sir Francis Wyatt.
Oh, but that's marvellous!

21:20.530 --> 21:23.850
My father served his father
at Boxley Manor when I was a child.

21:23.930 --> 21:25.890
He's exceedingly fond of me.

21:28.530 --> 21:30.810
No tongue, sir?

21:30.890 --> 21:32.850
No voice?

21:32.930 --> 21:38.130
I do hope that you'll remain,
Marshall Redwick.

21:38.210 --> 21:40.890
Together we might serve
the new Governor.

21:54.730 --> 21:56.730
(WHISPERS)

21:58.810 --> 22:00.810
(DOOR CLOSING)

22:08.330 --> 22:12.010
I love you. There, I've said it.

22:13.290 --> 22:15.690
Now you will remain in Jamestown.

22:17.490 --> 22:19.490
No, I won't.

22:21.930 --> 22:23.930
We will marry.

22:24.010 --> 22:25.970
Now you'll stay.

22:26.050 --> 22:28.010
No.

22:29.370 --> 22:31.370
I will not.

22:33.050 --> 22:35.610
Do you not see?

22:35.690 --> 22:38.210
Yeardley is deposed.

22:38.290 --> 22:41.130
Fortune favours us at last.
We can have land

22:41.210 --> 22:43.570
and whatever life we choose to make.

22:46.570 --> 22:48.890
You love me.

22:48.970 --> 22:50.930
I know you do.

22:51.970 --> 22:54.490
I have conceded.

22:54.570 --> 22:56.890
You have what you want.

22:56.970 --> 22:59.530
If I stay, I'll be your prisoner.

23:05.730 --> 23:09.490
Have you no notion of what
it costs me to say these things?

23:11.730 --> 23:16.330
Every breath of my being is locked
to a promise that I made myself.

23:16.410 --> 23:20.250
Never to love. Never love.

23:20.330 --> 23:23.250
Never.

23:23.330 --> 23:25.290
But I love you.

23:28.530 --> 23:30.530
I love you.

23:33.050 --> 23:35.050
Do you not hear it?

23:36.130 --> 23:38.130
I hear it.

23:41.490 --> 23:43.490
But you do not care.

23:45.970 --> 23:47.970
I care.

23:50.250 --> 23:52.250
Yes.

23:55.890 --> 23:57.890
But I'm leaving.

24:02.970 --> 24:04.970
Why?

24:07.970 --> 24:10.170
You'll know it when I'm gone.

24:14.210 --> 24:16.210
(SOFTLY) You break my heart.

24:19.690 --> 24:21.690
You break your own heart.

24:38.090 --> 24:40.090
(BANGING)

24:43.410 --> 24:45.410
(DOOR OPENS)

25:03.490 --> 25:06.770
James Read, we're searching for
Chacrow. Have you seen him about?

25:06.850 --> 25:09.370
No, I've not, Silas.
(SIGHS)

25:18.650 --> 25:23.050
James Read, I am in need
of your fine wisdom.

25:24.730 --> 25:26.850
Will you help me?

25:29.170 --> 25:31.170
(CLEARS THROAT)

25:33.010 --> 25:35.010
(SNIFFS)

25:44.690 --> 25:46.930
I, uh...

25:48.290 --> 25:50.290
(SNIFFS)

25:50.370 --> 25:52.490
Tam.

25:55.010 --> 25:57.690
I can't take back
what I said to you.

25:58.930 --> 26:01.770
And I can't undo what is done.

26:04.810 --> 26:07.690
There is sometimes about me...

26:09.490 --> 26:11.970
(STAMMERING) ..a bile...

26:14.050 --> 26:16.050
..which is cruel and bitter.

26:20.570 --> 26:22.730
So...

26:25.610 --> 26:30.010
..I thought, because my own pa...

26:30.090 --> 26:32.530
..was hating and brutal...

26:34.570 --> 26:41.170
..and because there's a storm
that howls through me

26:41.250 --> 26:43.450
when I so much as sit still...

26:48.730 --> 26:50.730
..I thought it was all justified.

26:53.890 --> 26:55.890
I see now it ain't never justified.

26:57.890 --> 27:00.450
I ain't a child. I'm a man.

27:03.810 --> 27:06.130
These words were given to me
by James Read...

27:07.770 --> 27:09.810
..but they're mine now.

27:11.170 --> 27:14.050
I'm a man, and you are the child.

27:15.250 --> 27:17.250
So I must behave as such.

27:24.370 --> 27:26.450
Will you have some bread?

27:27.850 --> 27:30.090
My wife, she makes...

27:30.170 --> 27:32.250
powerful bread.

27:38.130 --> 27:40.130
If you care for a pa...

27:42.330 --> 27:44.370
..then I'd be proud.

27:58.090 --> 28:00.090
(TAM SOBBING)

28:03.450 --> 28:06.210
Powerful bread.
(CHUCKLES)

28:13.210 --> 28:16.410
Fine work, captain.
These men will serve me well.

28:27.610 --> 28:29.930
Have them taken to my farm today.

28:33.290 --> 28:36.890
Many men like Pedro
will till the fields.

28:40.330 --> 28:44.970
Because we are the ones
he will leave in his will
for his children.

28:47.050 --> 28:49.050
Nobody will stop him.

28:51.010 --> 28:53.290
He does not have the power
of a governor,

28:53.370 --> 28:56.290
but everything is the same.

28:56.370 --> 28:59.530
And you see how
more like us come now.

29:01.690 --> 29:03.690
Perhaps it has started already.

29:05.970 --> 29:09.450
(CLICKS TONGUE) What are we to do?
(SIGHS)

29:13.970 --> 29:16.290
You know what you must do.

29:18.210 --> 29:20.570
Believe, Pedro.

29:25.810 --> 29:29.850
(SPEAKING KIMBUNDU)

29:48.250 --> 29:50.250
(SPEECH DROWNED OUT BY MUSIC)

30:06.850 --> 30:08.970
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

30:45.370 --> 30:48.290
(MAN CHANTING INDISTINCTLY)

30:48.370 --> 30:50.330
(OBJECT RATTLING)

30:59.650 --> 31:03.050
(SPEAKING ALGONQUIAN)

31:11.090 --> 31:13.330
(MAN CHANTING)
(CONTINUES IN ALGONQUIAN)

31:29.970 --> 31:32.210
(CONTINUES IN ALGONQUIAN)

32:04.490 --> 32:06.730
Mercy, why did you come here?

32:09.250 --> 32:13.690
I am afraid of ships.
I have such fears of the sea.

32:13.770 --> 32:17.210
I... I'd never been away
from my own village.

32:17.290 --> 32:22.210
But I bit on my lip and said to
myself...

32:23.810 --> 32:26.050
'Ain't it romantic?'

32:28.770 --> 32:31.930
Oh, Mercy.

32:32.010 --> 32:34.130
I love you so.

32:36.570 --> 32:38.850
I know you do, ma'am.

32:38.930 --> 32:41.250
Ain't no-one loves as you do.

32:41.330 --> 32:43.530
(BELL RINGING)

32:45.930 --> 32:49.650
(LIVELY MUSIC PLAYING)

33:22.410 --> 33:25.770
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

33:47.130 --> 33:50.290
I thought you had left us.
I did.

33:50.370 --> 33:52.770
I turned back.

33:52.850 --> 33:55.530
Will you come with me?

33:55.610 --> 33:57.610
How can I?

33:57.690 --> 34:00.850
I fought every day for my place here,
and now I've made it...

34:00.930 --> 34:04.610
Well, would you come with me,
anyway, if I told you that I loved
you?

34:06.450 --> 34:10.250
I promise you -
we will travel across this land

34:10.330 --> 34:13.489
and we will discover
all that can be discovered.

34:15.210 --> 34:19.130
And if we find
an unbearably beautiful field,

34:19.210 --> 34:22.570
then we will build our home
and we will have children.

34:22.650 --> 34:26.730
Children?
(CHUCKLES) Yes, children.

34:28.330 --> 34:30.570
Come with me.

34:30.650 --> 34:33.090
No.

34:36.770 --> 34:38.889
Yes.

34:38.969 --> 34:42.370
I'll need at least two or three weeks
to settle things here.

34:43.929 --> 34:46.489
Now is the moment.

34:46.570 --> 34:51.050
If you delay, you'll twist my mind,
and try and persuade me to stay
here.

34:51.130 --> 34:53.170
(CHUCKLES)

34:54.650 --> 34:57.610
Will you toast with me to Mercy?

35:06.290 --> 35:08.290
(CROWD CHEERING)

35:15.170 --> 35:18.930
(WHOOPING CALL)

35:54.530 --> 35:56.610
(CALLING CONTINUES)

36:04.290 --> 36:07.050
SILAS: Chacrow.

36:08.370 --> 36:11.010
(SPEAKING ALGONQUIAN)

37:08.650 --> 37:12.330
The food here in Jamestown is good.
The Governor must be very happy, eh?

37:12.410 --> 37:15.570
(LAUGHING)

37:15.650 --> 37:17.890
I wish we were eating
all of this for nothing.

37:17.970 --> 37:20.410
Did I tell the story
about how I met Maria, eh?

37:20.490 --> 37:24.850
All right, so, Maria... (LAUGHS)
..when she saw me, she said...

37:27.890 --> 37:30.530
(DISTORTED SPEECH)

37:30.610 --> 37:33.850
..when I see you.

37:38.450 --> 37:40.970
(MOUTHING)

37:42.410 --> 37:45.170
(PAMUNKEY CALLING)

37:46.450 --> 37:48.610
Maria.

37:50.810 --> 37:55.570
(SCREAMING)
(CALLING CONTINUES)

38:07.450 --> 38:09.450
(SCREAMING)

38:11.410 --> 38:13.530
(SCREAMS)

38:18.890 --> 38:21.330
(PAMUNKEY CALLING)

38:26.690 --> 38:29.210
(GASPING)

38:29.290 --> 38:31.770
Pedro, let's move.
We must get away.

38:31.850 --> 38:34.930
Hey, I am Pedro.

38:39.930 --> 38:42.490
(MARIA WHIMPERS)

38:48.490 --> 38:50.970
(WHOOPING CALL)

38:55.810 --> 38:58.730
(SOFT WHOOPING CALL)

39:01.330 --> 39:03.890
(SPEAKING ALGONQUIAN)

39:10.330 --> 39:13.410
(WHOOPING CALL)

39:13.490 --> 39:16.570
(PAMUNKEY CALLING)

39:19.490 --> 39:21.490
Oh, Christopher...

39:23.210 --> 39:27.410
(GASPS) Go to the town -
tell everyone there is an attack.

39:27.490 --> 39:29.450
I will hide him away.

39:29.530 --> 39:32.010
Go, Maria! Or you will not live.

39:35.250 --> 39:37.450
Silas! Hurry!

39:44.410 --> 39:46.730
You cannot stay here.
Where will they attack?

39:46.810 --> 39:49.050
There are many warriors
coming from far away

39:49.130 --> 39:52.170
and they will attack
all along the river.

39:52.250 --> 39:56.050
Go to the town. Run as fast
as you will to Jamestown.

39:56.130 --> 39:58.490
What will you do, Chacrow?

40:01.170 --> 40:03.370
I love my people.

40:06.490 --> 40:08.930
Go.
(CHACROW CRYING)

40:09.010 --> 40:12.290
WINGANUSKE: Henry. Henry.

40:18.090 --> 40:20.530
You are my family now, Henry.

40:20.610 --> 40:24.170
Winganuske,
I will make you a good husband.

40:32.370 --> 40:34.890
Stay close to me.

40:34.970 --> 40:37.530
(HORSE NEIGHS)

40:38.810 --> 40:41.370
Master Crabtree, we're under attack
from the Pamunkey.

40:41.450 --> 40:44.330
They're all about us. We need to
get back to the settlement.

40:44.410 --> 40:47.370
Get the doctor aboard my wagon.

40:48.130 --> 40:51.250
(GROANS)
Quickly.

40:51.330 --> 40:53.930
(PAMUNKEY CALLING)

40:57.930 --> 41:00.370
(SHRIEKS LOUDLY)
(GASPS)

41:00.450 --> 41:03.210
Henry, there's more of them
behind us.

41:03.290 --> 41:05.810
(ARROWS FLYING)

41:07.410 --> 41:10.090
We're trapped here.
(PAMUNKEY CALLING)

41:15.490 --> 41:17.850
These people know me as a conjuror.

41:17.930 --> 41:20.050
You said as much yourself,
Master Sharrow.

41:20.130 --> 41:23.770
Can you, between you,
carry the doctor and move at speed
down to the river?

41:23.850 --> 41:25.970
(ARROWS FLYING)
I'll walk towards them

41:26.050 --> 41:28.410
as the sorcerer who mystifies them.

41:28.490 --> 41:31.250
As I have their full attention,
you must move swiftly.

41:31.330 --> 41:34.290
Sir, they will kill you.

41:35.850 --> 41:40.730
Call to them. Tell them the conjuror
comes to put them under his spell.

41:44.850 --> 41:47.890
(SPEAKING ALGONQUIAN)

41:49.930 --> 41:52.370
(CHANTING)

41:55.330 --> 41:57.930
(CHANTING LOUDLY)

42:04.530 --> 42:07.290
(PAMUNKEY MAN SHOUTS IN ALGONQUIAN)
(PAMUNKEY CALLING)

42:07.370 --> 42:10.170
Pamunkey attack!

42:10.250 --> 42:13.530
James Read, Mistress Castell,
get beyond the settlement.

42:13.610 --> 42:16.890
Pamunkey attack! Pamunkey attack!
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

42:19.610 --> 42:21.610
Pamunkey attack!

42:22.930 --> 42:27.890
Everyone get into the settlement!
Someone bring the Governor!

42:27.970 --> 42:31.170
(CLAMOURING)

42:31.250 --> 42:34.450
(SCREAMING)

42:34.530 --> 42:36.850
Close the gate!
Pamunkey attack!

42:48.410 --> 42:50.610
(SPEAKING ALGONQUIAN)

42:54.610 --> 42:57.210
(YELLS IN ALGONQUIAN)

42:57.290 --> 43:00.570
(WHOOPS LOUDLY)
(PAMUNKEY CALLING)

